00:22:17,296 --> 00:22:19,330
or you're gonna miss your premiere.

273
00:22:20,583 --> 00:22:22,783
What would I do without you, Brooke Davis?

274
00:22:22,835 --> 00:22:25,837
Well, for starters, you'd wear a fez.

275
00:22:25,921 --> 00:22:27,839
Not okay.

276
00:22:27,907 --> 00:22:29,624
Come on.

277
00:22:29,675 --> 00:22:31,959
Your dad and your destiny are waiting.

278
00:22:44,690 --> 00:22:46,090
Thank you.

279
00:22:46,158 --> 00:22:48,776
Welcome.

280
00:22:48,828 --> 00:22:53,414
Uh, when my son Julian called me

281
00:22:53,482 --> 00:22:58,036
and asked me if I wanted
to make a movie with him,

282
00:22:58,120 --> 00:23:03,424
I thought it might be a
nice chance to reconnect.

283
00:23:03,492 --> 00:23:06,794
But that was that was
wishful thinking on my part,

284
00:23:06,846 --> 00:23:11,449
because I was gone so often
while he was, uh, growing up

285
00:23:11,517 --> 00:23:15,854
that we never really
connected in the first place.

286
00:23:15,938 --> 00:23:18,173
And that's a shame.

287
00:23:20,676 --> 00:23:24,195
Whenever I finish a movie,
I... I have this expression...

288
00:23:24,280 --> 00:23:26,581
"let's kick it out of the nest...

289
00:23:26,649 --> 00:23:29,033
and see if it flies."

290
00:23:29,118 --> 00:23:32,871
Well, son, we kicked you out of the nest.

291
00:23:32,955 --> 00:23:36,908
And it has been a
pleasure watching you soar.

292
00:23:38,527 --> 00:23:40,295
I hope you all agree.

293
00:23:45,668 --> 00:23:47,835
I'll see you in a bit.

294
00:24:00,349 --> 00:24:02,350
Julian. It's starting.

295
00:24:02,401 --> 00:24:05,386
Yeah, I know. I think I'm
just gonna wait till it's over.

296
00:24:08,057 --> 00:24:10,608
Those were some nice things
your father said about you.

297
00:24:10,693 --> 00:24:12,944
Yeah.

298
00:24:13,028 --> 00:24:14,696
You sure you don't want
to come back inside?

299
00:24:14,747 --> 00:24:17,732
Yeah, but you should go
watch it with an audience.

300
00:24:17,783 --> 00:24:20,835
I want you to see how good you
are as an actor and a writer.

301
00:24:22,338 --> 00:24:24,205
I was in good hands.

302
00:24:24,256 --> 00:24:26,741
And everything's gonna be okay.

303
00:24:26,792 --> 00:24:27,959
You know why?

304
00:24:28,043 --> 00:24:30,712
Because it already is.

305
00:24:33,515 --> 00:24:35,934
Opened with a sex scene.
Nice work, Polanski.

306
00:24:36,018 --> 00:24:38,019
Good luck explaining that one to the kid.

307
00:24:41,390 --> 00:24:43,274
You're not watching it either, huh?

308
00:24:43,359 --> 00:24:44,392
Nope.

309
00:24:44,443 --> 00:24:46,144
Were you grossed out, too?

310
00:24:48,080 --> 00:24:50,431
Come on. We should go get a drink.

311
00:24:52,785 --> 00:24:55,253
